00:14:52.620 --> 00:14:57.230
Today, bottom left, the Panama
Canal is the beating heart

00:14:57.230 --> 00:15:02.200
of the US economy as trade
goods flow back and forth.

00:15:02.200 --> 00:15:06.460
And it's challenged, it's not
geopolitical challenged --

00:15:06.460 --> 00:15:10.990
nation on nation -- but
it's narcotics, it's gangs,

00:15:10.990 --> 00:15:16.460
it's natural disasters,
it's refugees here as well.

00:15:16.460 --> 00:15:21.430
All of it leads to
significant maritime activity

00:15:21.430 --> 00:15:25.800
by our Coastguard working together
with the Navy, law enforcement

00:15:25.800 --> 00:15:27.650
of course taking the lead.

00:15:27.650 --> 00:15:31.350
Let's go to the top of
the world; the Arctic.

00:15:31.350 --> 00:15:36.730
This is USS Jeanette, it was
the ship sent to the Arctic

00:15:36.730 --> 00:15:42.950
in the 1870s, when many
cartographers/geographers still had

00:15:42.950 --> 00:15:48.120
